        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add Sakana AI provider support",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAdds first-class Sakana AI provider support to CodexBar.\r\n\r\nThis introduces a new `sakana` provider that validates Sakana API access, displays plan-level quota from the Sakana console, and integrates Sakana branding into the app UI.\r\n\r\n## What Changed\r\n\r\n- Added new provider id: `sakana`\r\n- Added Sakana AI settings UI\r\n  - Secure API key field\r\n  - Cookie source selector\r\n  - Auto Browser cookie mode\r\n  - Manual cookie header fallback\r\n  - Links to Sakana Overview, Billing, and Pricing\r\n- Added Sakana API key validation through `GET /v1/models`\r\n  - Confirms `fugu` and `fugu-ultra` availability\r\n  - Does not make generation calls during refresh\r\n- Added Sakana console quota parsing\r\n  - Primary window: 5-hour quota\r\n  - Secondary window: weekly quota\r\n  - Plan name displayed when available\r\n- Added browser-cookie based quota fetching from `console.sakana.ai`\r\n- Added official Sakana logo asset and colored brand rendering\r\n- Added provider docs and README fork notes\r\n- Added unit coverage for settings, API validation, quota parsing, cookie/login behavior, and config validation\r\n\r\n## Security Notes\r\n\r\n- No API keys, cookies, session tokens, or local config files are committed.\r\n- Documentation uses placeholders only.\r\n- Sakana API keys and console cookies are treated as secrets.\r\n- Quota fetching only reads the authenticated console pages needed for usage display.\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- `swift build --target CodexBar`\r\n- `swift build --target CodexBarCore`\r\n- `swift build --product CodexBarCLI`\r\n- `./Scripts/lint.sh format`\r\n- Manual verification with Sakana API validation and console quota display",
